{
  "texts": [
    "When compared to the non-preemption task scheduling model with LRU cache, the improvements are 1.32%, 7.27%, 10.2%, and 9.13% for the same cache sizes.",
    "The approach successfully schedules all tasks in the test data sets, showing improvement in WCET reduction and overall execution time.",
    "This method ensures that tasks are completed before their deadlines while minimizing the total execution time, proving effective for real-time systems with cache constraints.Zhang et al. [97] propose a method for predicting WCET and energy consumption of programs using the Levenberg-Marquardt (L-M) algorithm [98].",
    "It integrates static and dynamic analysis methods to estimate WCET and energy consumption based on program features such as dynamic instruction features.",
    "The approach uses a neural network trained with the L-M algorithm to enhance prediction accuracy, comparing favourably to traditional regression methods."
  ]
}